note: Subject/Participant Identifier (primary key)
An identifier used by GREGoR research centers to identify a set of participants for their internal tracking
GREGoR Center to which the participant is originally associated
Consent group pertaining to this participant's data
Is the originating GREGoR Center likely able to recontact this participant
Text description of any genetic testing for individual conducted prior to enrollment
Case specific PubMed ID if applicable
Identifier for family
subject_id for father; 0 if not available
subject_id for mother; 0 if not available
subject_id for twins, triplets, etc; 0 if not available
Text description of individual relationship to proband in family, especially useful to capture relationships when connecting distant relatives and connecting relatives not studied
Other proband relationship not captured in enumeration above
Biological sex assigned at birth (aligned with All of Us). If individual has a known DSD / not expected sex chromosome karyotype, this can be noted in the phenotype information section.
Optional free-text field to describe known discrepancies between 'sex' value (female=>XX, male=>XY) and actual sex chromosome karyotype
Self/submitter-reported race (OMB categories)
Self/submitter-reported ethnicity (OMB categories)
Additional specific ancestry description free text beyond what is captured by OMB race/ethnicity categories

Age at last observation, aka age in years at the last time the center can vouch for the accuracy phenotype data. For conditions with later age of onset, this field lets users know if individuals marked as unaffected were younger or older than the age when the phenotype is expected to appear.
Indicate affected status of individual (overall with respect to primary phenotype in the family). Note: Affected participants must have entry in phenotype table.
human-readable \"Phenotypic one-line summary\" for why this individual is of interest. Could be the same as the term_details value in the Phenotype table. Strongly encourage/required for proband.
age in years at which consent was originally obtained
Identifier for family (primary key)
Indicate if consanguinity is present or suspected within a family
Free text description of any additional consanguinity details
name of file (renamed from pedigree_image because it can contain a PED file or image)
Free text description of other family structure/pedigree file caption or legend.
Details about family history that do not fit into structured fields. Family relationship terms should be relative to the proband.
primary key
Subject/Participant Identifier
modifier of a term where the additional details are not supported/available as a term in HPO
identifier for an analyte from a primary biosample source (primary key)
analyte derived from the primary_biosample. The actual thing you're sticking into a machine to analyze/sequence
details about how the analyte or original biosample was extracted or processed
Tissue type of biosample taken from the participant that the analyte was extracted or processed from (for unknown can use tissue - UBERON:0000479), e.g. skin, liver, brain
Optional ID for the biosample; allows for linking of multiple analytes extracted or processed from the same biosample
Free text to capture information not in structured fields
If applicable to disease (suspected mosaic), is the tissue from an affected source or an unaffected source?
age or participant in years at biosample collection
The list of drugs patient is on, at the time of sample collection. This information is helpful during analysis of metabolomics and immune asssays. Free Text
If the patient was fasting, when the sample was collected. this is relevant when analyzing metabolomics data. Free Text
his is relevant when analyzing metabolomics data
passage_number is relevant for fibroblast cultures and possibly iPSC.
time (in hours) from collection to freezing the sample. delayed freeze turns out to be useful / important info for PaxGene blood (for RNA isolation).
details regarding sample transformation
identifier for experiment_short_read (primary key)
identifier used in the data file (e.g. VCF header / LIMS ID)
Library prep kit used
sequenced read length (bp); GREGoR RCs do paired end sequencing, so is the example of 100bp indicates 2x100bp.
Which capture kit is used. Can be missing if RC receives external data
name and path of bed file uploaded to workspace
Date of data generation (First sequencing date)
insert size the protocol targets for DNA fragments
sequencing platform used for the experiment
identifier for aligned_short_read (primary key)
identifier for experiment
name and path of file with aligned reads
name and path of index file corresponding to aligned reads file
md5 checksum for file
Software including version number
Mean coverage of either the genome or the targeted regions
brief description of the analysis pipeline used for producing the file; perhaps a DOI or link to something like a WDL file or github repository
identifier for a set of experiments (primary key)
unique key for table (anvil requirement)
identifier for experiment set
name and path of the file with variant calls
md5 checksum for file
variant calling software used including version number
types of variants called
brief description of the analysis pipeline used for producing the file; perhaps a link to something like a WDL file or github repository
